cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.NA, cs.SI 

The paper deals with the problem of clustering and embedding data that is modeled as being drawn from a smooth manifold. This is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) where manifold learning techniques are used to extract low-dimensional representations of high-dimensional data. The paper also discusses the use of spectral clustering (cs.IT) and low-rank matrix factorization (cs.NA) techniques in the proposed algorithm. Finally, the paper presents experimental results on simulated and real datasets, which is a common practice in the field of signal processing (cs.SI).
